# Server vs Client Components

## Default Rule
**All components are Server Components by default.**
Never add `"use client"` unless the component genuinely requires it.

---

## When to Add `"use client"`

Add `"use client"` ONLY when the component directly uses:

| Trigger | Examples |
|---|---|
| React state | `useState`, `useReducer` |
| React effects | `useEffect`, `useLayoutEffect` |
| React refs | `useRef`, `useImperativeHandle` |
| Event handlers | `onClick`, `onChange`, `onSubmit` |
| Browser APIs | `window`, `document`, `localStorage`, `navigator` |
| Custom hooks from `src/hooks/` | `useScrollPosition`, `useMediaQuery`, `useForm` |
| Animation libraries | Framer Motion, etc. |
| Context consumers | `useContext` |

---

## The Leaf Rule — Push `"use client"` as deep as possible

Break large components into smaller ones so that only the interactive leaf needs `"use client"`.

```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT — Server wraps a tiny Client leaf
// Navbar.jsx — NO "use client"
import NavMobile from './NavMobile'   // "use client"
import NavLink from './NavLink'       // "use client"

export default function Navbar() {
  return (
    <nav>
      <NavLink href="/about">About</NavLink>
      <NavMobile />
    </nav>
  )
}

// ❌ WRONG — entire Navbar is client just because of mobile menu state
"use client"
export default function Navbar() {
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false)
  // ...
}
```

---

## Server Component Patterns

### Data fetching — do it directly in the Server Component
```jsx
// app/(marketing)/products/page.jsx — Server Component
import { getProducts } from '@/lib/api/products'
import ProductGrid from '@/features/products/ProductGrid'

export default async function ProductsPage() {
  const products = await getProducts()   // ✅ fetch server-side
  return <ProductGrid products={products} />
}
```

### Never fetch data in a Client Component
```jsx
// ❌ WRONG — fetching in a Client Component
"use client"
export default function ProductGrid() {
  const [products, setProducts] = useState([])
  useEffect(() => {
    fetch('/api/products').then(...)   // ❌ unnecessary client fetch
  }, [])
}
```

---

## Client Component Patterns

### Always declare `"use client"` as the very first line
```jsx
// ✅ Correct
"use client"

import { useState } from 'react'

export default function FAQAccordion({ items }) {
  const [openIndex, setOpenIndex] = useState(null)
  // ...
}
```

### Client Components can only receive serializable props from Server Components
```jsx
// ✅ Serializable — strings, numbers, plain objects, arrays
<ProductCard name="Transformer" price={1200} tags={["new"]} />

// ❌ Not serializable — functions, class instances, Dates as objects
<ProductCard onFavorite={() => {}} />   // ❌ pass handler differently
```

